Build it

00:00:09.370 --> 00:00:15.710
Seamster at instructables.com made this R2-D2
or the R2 double D2 bra as he likes to call

00:00:15.710 --> 00:00:24.329
it, equipped with lights and sounds! Made
from paper mache and the lights and sounds

00:00:24.329 --> 00:00:30.179
from an old R2 D2 toy. He also has an easier
duct tape version for novice crafters.&nbsp;Find

00:00:30.179 --> 00:00:31.199
the link below.

00:00:31.199 --> 00:00:36.430
Calvin Seibert has taken the art of making
sandcastles to the next level with these geometric

00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:41.340
shapes. He says it's like a test because nature
is always against you and time is always running

00:00:41.340 --> 00:00:46.100
out. He starts by making the basic shapes
with his hands and uses a simple plastic spackle

00:00:46.100 --> 00:00:50.550
tool to do the precision work. And he works
on them until the tides come and wash them

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:53.210
away leaving him a clean new canvas.&nbsp;

00:00:53.210 --> 00:00:58.320
Tony Swatton is a blacksmith that recreates
weapons from TV shows and movies. Here he

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:04.100
is forging the sword of Jamie Lanister from
Game of Thrones. Others include he man's sword,

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:11.360
batmans batarangs, raphaels sais, oddjobs
hat, and finns golden sword. Check out his

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:13.320
fantastic youtube channel for more.&nbsp;

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:14.890
Draw It

00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:20.680
Artist StarRovias re creates modern day video
games into old school Atari cartridges. Including

00:01:20.680 --> 00:01:27.340
Skyrim, Fallout3, grand theft auto, minecraft,
and mass effect. Check out the full collection

00:01:27.340 --> 00:01:28.910
at her deviant art page.&nbsp;

00:01:28.910 --> 00:01:35.160
Artist Adam Spizak makes some amazing illustrations
of popular TV characters such as Dexter, Rick

00:01:35.160 --> 00:01:41.650
from walking dead, Don from Mad Men, and Walter
from Breaking Bad. All are available to purchase

00:01:41.650 --> 00:01:43.920
so check out the website in the link below.&nbsp;

